freetext.SYSTEMIC_REACTION_OTHER: Brain fog.  Unusual trouble with word recall, recall of events, trouble focusing. Also runny nose and sore throat.  Those have been coming on  for a few days.  I had not really associated them with the vaccine.    Today I learned that a person I had contact with last week is covid positive and get husband is pretty sick with it
I had a few days where my tongue seemed partially numb.   But not today.

My tongue feels tingly or numb.    Some soreness around my neck, a strange, slightly woozy feeling, like the aura of a bad cold or flu.  I don't want to drink because I feel nauseated and nothing tastes right.
Numb/tingling tongue,. Brain fog, trouble with word recall. And focus.

The "rash" I'm checking was on the front of my shoulder,a few inches away from the injection.  It was an irregular, reddish blotch with some raised white spots, like a hive.  That was last night.  It is fading today.  Not a problem, just weird.
